'''金星生命'''是指[[金星|金星]]上可能存在的[[生命|生命]]，迄今为止，人类尚未观测到金星生命的存在。金星是距离地球最近的[[行星|行星]]，且金星在质量、大小、密度上与地球十分接近，在20世纪60年代金星探测任务揭示了其表面的极端环境之前，人们一度认为金星比[[火星|火星]]更可能存在生命。

金星比地球更靠近太阳，剧烈的温室效应使得金星表面的温度达到约735开尔文（462°C），其地表大气压力是地球的九十多倍，生物难以生存在金星地表。但是[[金星大气层|金星大气]]高层温度、气压较低，[[嗜極生物|嗜極微生物]]可能生存于此处<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newscientist.com/article/dn2843-acidic-clouds-of-venus-could-harbour-life.html|trans_title=金星的酸云可能孕育生命|title=Acidic clouds of Venus could harbour life|work=New Scientist|first=Stuart|last=Clark|date=2003-09-26|accessdate=2015-12-30|archive-date=2015-05-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150516203938/http://www.newscientist.com/article/dn2843-acidic-clouds-of-venus-could-harbour-life.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|trans_title=金星云或为生命的港湾|author1=Redfern|author2=Martin|date=2004-05-24|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/3746583.stm|title="Venus clouds 'might harbour life'"|work=BBC News|accessdate=2015|archive-date=2020-09-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200916211157/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/3746583.stm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Dartnell2015">{{cite journal |title=Constraints on a potential aerial biosphere on Venus: I. Cosmic rays |journal=Icarus |date=September 2015 |last1=Dartnell |first1=Lewis R. |last2=Nordheim |first2=Tom Andre |last3= Patel |first3=Manish R. |last4=Mason |first4= Jonathon P. |volume=257 |pages=396–405 |doi=10.1016/j.icarus.2015.05.006 |display-authors=etal|bibcode = 2015Icar..257..396D }}</ref>。2020年9月的一项研究显示金星大气层中存在有[[磷化氢|磷化氢]]，这可能是金星生命存在的迹象。<ref name="NatGeoDrake" /><ref name="NA-20200914" /><ref name="NYT-20200914" />

== 表面状况 ==
由于金星表面完全被浓密的大气和云层覆盖，因而在探测器抵达金星之前，人们对金星表面的认知基本来自于推测，直至20世纪中叶，人们仍然认为金星表面环境与地球相似，并可能存在生命。1870年，英国天文学家{{tsl|en|Richard A. Proctor|理查德·普罗克特}}认为，金星赤道附近不可能存在生命，但是两极则有可能。<ref>Proctor, Richard A., ''Other Worlds Than Ours: The Plurality of Worlds Studied Under the Light of Recent Scientific Researches''. New York : J.A. Hill and Co., 1870. s. 94.</ref>当时的[[科學幻想|科幻]]小说家对金星表面进行了大胆的想象和描述，在[[虛構作品中的金星|他们的笔下]]，金星表面或者遍布森林，或者拥有一个由[[石油|石油]]或[[碳酸水|碳酸水]]构成的广袤海洋。

1958年，迈尔（C. Mayer）等人通过微波观测发现金星存在温度高达600开尔文（约326℃）的高温源<ref>{{cite journal| journal =Astrophysical Journal| volume= 127| date=1958| pages =1–9 | doi=10.1086/146433| title=Observations of Venus at 3.15-CM Wave Length| url =https://archive.org/details/sim_astrophysical-journal_1958-05_127_3/page/1| first1=C. H. | last1= Mayer| first2= T. P. | last2=McCollough | first3=R. M. | last3=Sloanaker | bibcode=1958ApJ...127....1M}}</ref>，但当时科学家们对此高温源位于金星表面还是电离层存在争议。1962年12月，[[水手2号|水手2号]]首次飞掠金星并对金星进行了科学探测，科学家根据水手2号发回的数据估计金星表面温度大概为500摄氏度<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nasa.gov/multimedia/imagegallery/image_feature_964.html|title=Mariner 2|first=NASA Content|last=Administrator|date=2015-03-06|website=NASA|accessdate=2020-09-18|archive-date=2019-12-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191217201955/https://www.nasa.gov/multimedia/imagegallery/image_feature_964.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。随着{{tsl|en|List of missions to Venus|金星探测}}的持续进行，越来越多的证据表明金星的自然环境的极端恶劣，如大气中存在着大量硫酸云、极高的地表气压和温度<ref name="#1">{{Cite web|url=http://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.php?feature=6100|title=Venus Air Pressure|website=NASA/JPL|accessdate=2020-09-18|archive-date=2020-09-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200916223741/https://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.php?feature=6100|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="#1"/>，地球上的生命形式难于在金星的恶劣环境下生存。

== 过去的适居性 ==

在金星的[[失控溫室效應|温室效应失控]]导致其丧失绝大多数水分之前，金星表面可以存在液态水，可能形成微生物生命<ref name= "Forbes">Bruce Dorminey, [https://www.forbes.com/sites/brucedorminey/2016/03/28/venus-likely-had-past-life-next-step-is-finding-it/ "Venus Likely Had Past Life; Next Step Is Finding It"] {{Wayback|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/brucedorminey/2016/03/28/venus-likely-had-past-life-next-step-is-finding-it/ |date=20200916214750 }}, ''Forbes'', 28 March 2016.</ref>。假设宜居带附近的行星上的水与地球上的水具有相同的起源，则[[後期重轟炸期|後期重轟炸期]]及之后，液态水可能存在于金星表面长达6亿年，这段时间足以进化出简单生命。但不同的研究对金星表面液态水的存在时长的估计差距很大，从几百万年至数十亿年不等。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.esa.int/Our_Activities/Space_Science/Venus_Express/Was_Venus_once_a_habitable_planet |title=Was Venus once a habitable planet? |date=2010-06-24 |publisher=[[欧洲空间局|European Space Agency]] |accessdate=2016-05-22 |archive-date=2018-12-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181205103232/http://www.esa.int/Our_Activities/Space_Science/Venus_Express/Was_Venus_once_a_habitable_planet |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.universetoday.com/67240/was-venus-once-a-waterworld/ |title=Was Venus once a waterworld? |date=2010-06-24 |author=Nancy Atkinson |publisher=[[Universe_Today|Universe Today]] |accessdate=2016-05-22 |archive-date=2019-03-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190328043717/https://www.universetoday.com/67240/was-venus-once-a-waterworld/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.space.com/283-venus-alive-signs.html |title=Was Venus Alive? 'The Signs are Probably There' |date=2004-08-26 |author=Henry Bortman |publisher={{tsl|en|Space.com||Space.com}} |accessdate=2016-05-22 |archive-date=2016-03-04 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20160304024104/http://www.space.com/283-venus-alive-signs.html |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nasa.gov/feature/goddard/2016/nasa-climate-modeling-suggests-venus-may-have-been-habitable |title=NASA Climate Modeling Suggests Venus May Have Been Habitable |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=2016-08-11 |website=NASA.gov |publisher=[[美国国家航空航天局|NASA]] |access-date=2016-08-15 |archive-date=2019-01-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190127181128/https://www.nasa.gov/feature/goddard/2016/nasa-climate-modeling-suggests-venus-may-have-been-habitable/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|arxiv=1608.00706 |title=Was Venus the First Habitable World of our Solar System?' |journal=Geophysical Research Letters |volume=43 |issue=16 |pages=8376–8383 |date=2016-08-02 |author=Michael J. Way |doi=10.1002/2016GL069790 |bibcode=2016GeoRL..43.8376W |pmid=28408771 |pmc=5385710 }}</ref>2019年的一份研究指出，金星表面存在地表水并且较为宜居的时间可能长达30亿年，这一宜居状态可能一直持续到7至7.5亿年前<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sci-news.com/space/planetaryscience/habitable-venus-07619.html|title=Venus May Have Been Habitable for Three Billion Years {{!}} Planetary Science {{!}} Sci-News.com|website=Breaking Science News {{!}} Sci-News.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-24|archive-date=2019-09-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190924053603/http://www.sci-news.com/space/planetaryscience/habitable-venus-07619.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref>，如果此结论正确，生命完全有足够的时间进化到大气层中。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dailygalaxy.com/my_weblog/2012/06/did-the-early-venus-harbor-life-weekend-feature.html |title=Did the Early Venus Harbor Life? (Weekend Feature) |date=2012-06-02 |publisher=The Daily Galaxy |accessdate=2016-05-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171028012143/http://www.dailygalaxy.com/my_weblog/2012/06/did-the-early-venus-harbor-life-weekend-feature.html |archive-date=2017-10-28 |dead-url=yes }}</ref> 

目前人类对金星表面的探测很不充分，如果人类向金星发射能承受金星极端地表环境的探测器并对其表面物质分析，或许可以找到生物存在的相关证据<ref name=":0" />。然而金星的地表十分年轻，仅有5亿年左右的年龄<ref name="Strom1994">{{cite journal |last=Strom |first=Robert G. |author2=Schaber, Gerald G. |author3=Dawson, Douglas D. |date=1994-05-25 |title=The global resurfacing of Venus |journal=[[地球物理研究期刊|Journal of Geophysical Research]] |volume=99 |issue=E5 |pages=10899–10926 |doi=10.1029/94JE00388 |bibcode=1994JGR....9910899S |url=https://zenodo.org/record/1231347 |access-date=2020-09-18 |archive-date=2020-09-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200916233329/https://zenodo.org/record/1231347 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，这意味着即使在这之前金星上有生物存在，人类也很难在金星表面找到比这更早的生物的化石{{r|下一站}}，但仍可能找到一些[[生命印迹|生命印迹]]。<ref name=Shiga>{{cite web |url=https://www.newscientist.com/article/dn12769-did-venuss-ancient-oceans-incubate-life/ |title=Did Venus's ancient oceans incubate life? |date=2007-10-10 |author=David Shiga |publisher=[[新科學人|New Scientist]] |accessdate=2016-05-22 |archive-date=2019-03-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190328005309/https://www.newscientist.com/article/dn12769-did-venuss-ancient-oceans-incubate-life/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

== 大气的适居性 ==
===大气状况===
{{主条目|金星大氣層}}
金星拥有比地球更厚重与浓密的[[大气层|大气层]]，其主要成分为[[二氧化碳|二氧化碳]]，大气层分布有浓厚的主要由硫酸组成的云层。大量的20世纪下半叶，科学家在对[[金星計劃|金星計劃]]、[[先驱者金星计划|先驱者金星计划]]、[[麥哲倫號金星探測器|麥哲倫號金星探測任务]]返回的数据进行分析时发现，金星的高层大气同时存在[[羰基硫|羰基硫]]、[[硫化氫|硫化氫]]和[[二氧化硫|二氧化硫]]，羰基硫不容易通过无机过程产生，而硫化氢会自发与二氧化硫会反应，这说明金星上存在产生这两种物质的机制。此前还有金星探测器发现金星云层下存在[[氯气|氯气]]。<ref>{{cite book|author=David Harry Grinspoon|title=Venus Revealed: A New Look Below the Clouds of Our Mysterious Twin Planet|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Un_vAAAAMAAJ|year=1997|publisher=fdffdsdasfdfgjhkjlkuytdsfghjkl;Addison-Wesley Pub.|isbn=978-0-201-40655-9}}</ref>二氧化碳、二氧化硫及[[水蒸气|水蒸气]]在太阳的照射下可在上层大气中发生[[光化学|光化学反应]]产生[[硫酸|硫酸]]。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://m.esa.int/Our_Activities/Space_Science/Venus_Express/Acid_clouds_and_lightning |title=Venus Express: Acid clouds and lightning |work=European Space Agency (ESA) |accessdate=2016-09-08 |archive-date=2019-03-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190328164734/http://m.esa.int/Our_Activities/Space_Science/Venus_Express/Acid_clouds_and_lightning |dead-url=no }}</ref>

金星地表附近不可能存在生命，但是距离金星地表50公里附近的大气温度、压力及太阳辐射水平适宜，微生物可能栖身于此处。<ref>[http://www.maik.ru/cgi-perl/search.pl?type=abstract&name=solsys&number=1&year=12&page=41  Venus as a Natural Laboratory for Search of Life in High Temperature Conditions: Events on the Planet on March 1, 1982] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151107053831/http://www.maik.ru/cgi-perl/search.pl?type=abstract&name=solsys&number=1&year=12&page=41 |date=2015-11-07 }}, L. V. Ksanfomality, published in [http://www.maik.ru/contents/solsys/solsys1_12v46cont.htm ''Astronomicheskii Vestnik'', Vol. 46, No. 1, 2012] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304051810/http://www.maik.ru/contents/solsys/solsys1_12v46cont.htm |date=2016-03-04 }}.</ref><ref name=Landis2003b /><ref name='Dartnell2015'/>金星赤道附近云层存在紫外线频段下反射率较低的“暗区”，科学家因此猜测金星云层可能有吸收紫外线的化学物质，这些物质可能保护金星生命免遭紫外线的破坏<ref>{{cite news |title=科学家揭开金星紫外线之谜 |url=http://news.sciencenet.cn/htmlpaper/20081291515517354384.html |accessdate=2020-09-18 |agency=科学网 |date=2008 |archive-date=2012-07-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120719160504/http://news.sciencenet.cn/htmlpaper/20081291515517354384.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，也有科学家猜测金星云层中的生物会吸收紫外线甚至金星生命自身即有利用紫外线的能力。<ref>[https://astronomy.com/news/2019/08/mysterious-dark-patches-in-venus-clouds-are-affecting-the-weather-there Mysterious dark patches in Venus' clouds are affecting the weather there.] {{Wayback|url=https://astronomy.com/news/2019/08/mysterious-dark-patches-in-venus-clouds-are-affecting-the-weather-there |date=20200916190958 }} What the dark patches are is still a mystery, though astronomers dating back to Carl Sagan have suggested they could be extraterrestrial microorganisms. Erica Naone, ''Astronomy''. 29 August 2019.</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abc.net.au/cgi-bin/common/printfriendly.pl?/news/scitech/2002/09/item20020926135029_1.htm|title=Venus could be a haven for life|work=ABC News|date=2002-09-28|accessdate=2015-12-30|archive-date=2016-05-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160530065215/http://www.abc.net.au/cgi-bin/common/printfriendly.pl?%2Fnews%2Fscitech%2F2002%2F09%2Fitem20020926135029_1.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Schulze">{{cite journal |title=Reassessing the Possibility of Life on Venus: Proposal for an Astrobiology Mission |journal=Astrobiology |date=2004-07-05 |last1=Schulze-Makuch |first1=Dirk |last2=Irwin |first2=Louis N. |volume=2 |issue=2 |pages=197–202 |doi=10.1089/15311070260192264 |bibcode = 2002AsBio...2..197S |pmid=12469368}}</ref>

=== 可能的生物标志物 ===

2020年1月，天文学家称有证据表明金星表面的[[火山#太陽系中其他的火山|火山]]仍处于活跃状态<ref>{{cite journal |author1=冯丽妃 |title=金星火山仍然活跃 |journal=中国科学报 |date=2020-07-22 |url=http://news.sciencenet.cn/htmlnews/2020/7/443178.shtm |accessdate=2020-09-18 |archive-date=2020-07-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200725011836/http://news.sciencenet.cn/htmlnews/2020/7/443178.shtm |dead-url=no }}</ref>，火山活动释放的物质可能是金星大气中可能存在的微生物的营养来源<ref name="NYT-20200109">{{cite news |last=Hall |first=Sannon |title=Volcanoes on Venus Might Still Be Smoking - Planetary science experiments on Earth suggest that the sun's second planet might have ongoing volcanic activity. |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/09/science/venus-volcanoes-active.html |date=2020-01-09 |work=[[纽约时报|The New York Times]] |accessdate=2020-01-10 |archive-date=2020-01-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200109234012/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/09/science/venus-volcanoes-active.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="SCI-20200103">{{cite journal |author=Filiberto, Justin |title=Present-day volcanism on Venus as evidenced from weathering rates of olivine |date=2020-01-03 |journal=[[科学_(期刊)|Science]] |volume=6 |number=1 |doi=10.1126/sciadv.aax7445 |page=eaax7445|pmid=31922004 |pmc=6941908 |bibcode=2020SciA....6.7445F }}</ref><ref name="AB-20180912">{{cite journal |author=Limaye, Sanjay S. |title=Venus' Spectral Signatures and the Potential for Life in the Clouds |date=2018-09-12 |journal={{tsl|en|Astrobiology (journal)||Astrobiology}} |volume=18 |number=9 |doi=10.1089/ast.2017.1783 |pmid=29600875 |pmc=6150942 |pages=1181–1198 |bibcode=2018AsBio..18.1181L }}</ref>。

2020年9月，一个来自英国的科学家团队在金星大气中探测到了[[磷化氢|磷化氢]]气体。磷化氢气体难以在金星大气中稳定存在，此次探测出磷化氢证明金星上存在产生磷化氢的途径，目前人类尚未弄清这些磷化氢的来源。在地球上，磷化氢的主要由[[厭氧生物|厌氧微生物]]代谢产生，而在金星的条件下，已知的[[非生物因子|非生命过程]]不会产生这么多的磷化氢<ref name="NatGeoDrake">{{cite news |last1=Drake |first1=Nadia |title=Possible sign of life on Venus stirs up heated debate |url=https://www.nationalgeographic.com/science/2020/09/possible-sign-of-life-found-on-venus-phosphine-gas/ |accessdate=2020-09-14 |work=National Geographic |date=2020-09-14 |archive-date=2020-09-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200914153820/https://www.nationalgeographic.com/science/2020/09/possible-sign-of-life-found-on-venus-phosphine-gas/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="NA-20200914">{{cite journal |author=Greaves, Jane S. |display-authors=et al. |title=Phosphine gas in the cloud decks of Venus |trans_title=金星云层中的磷化氢气体 |url=https://www.nature.com/articles/s41550-020-1174-4 |date=2020-09-14 |journal=[[自然·天文学|Nature Astronomy]] |doi=10.1038/s41550-020-1174-4 |accessdate=2020-09-14 |archive-date=2020-09-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200914150731/https://www.nature.com/articles/s41550-020-1174-4 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="NYT-20200914">{{cite news |last1=Stirone |first1=Shannon |last2=Chang |first2=Kenneth |last3=Overbye |first3=Dennis |title=Life on Venus? Astronomers See a Signal in Its Clouds - The detection of a gas in the planet’s atmosphere could turn scientists’ gaze to a planet long overlooked in the search for extraterrestrial life. |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/09/14/science/venus-life-clouds.html |date=2020-09-14 |work=[[纽约时报|The New York Times]] |accessdate=2020-09-14 |archive-date=2020-09-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200914151019/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/09/14/science/venus-life-clouds.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。金星上磷化氢的产生机制可能是人类尚未发现的某种化学过程或是地质过程，亦有可能系某种微生物群落的代谢活动。<ref>{{cite news |author1=张梦然 |title=金星大气中首次探测到磷化氢 |url=http://digitalpaper.stdaily.com/http_www.kjrb.com/kjrb/images/2020-09/15/02/KJRB2020091502.pdf |accessdate=2020-09-18 |work=科技日报 |date=2020-09-15}}</ref>後續有研究團隊認為先前該研究引用的電波訊號所反應的是[[二氧化硫|二氧化硫]]而非磷化氫。<ref>{{cite news |author1=Emma stein |title=金星沒有生命，曾令人振奮的磷化氫訊號只是普通二氧化硫 |url=https://technews.tw/2021/02/11/phosphine-venus-sulfur-dioxide-spectral-line-dilution-microbe/ |accessdate=2021-03-04 |work=科技新报 |date=2021-02-11}}</ref>

